Come. Jump!

27
00:01:30,156 --> 00:01:31,324
-Jump!
-(Snoop whimpers)

28
00:01:32,116 --> 00:01:33,367
(speaking French)

29
00:01:33,451 --> 00:01:34,744
(Snoop whimpers)

30
00:01:34,827 --> 00:01:37,288
(groans) Jump. Jump.

31
00:01:38,372 --> 00:01:39,415
(in English)
...and then that leads me

32
00:01:39,498 --> 00:01:41,042
to an interesting story.

33
00:01:41,125 --> 00:01:43,127
And I decide to put you
in the book I'm writing.

34
00:01:43,211 --> 00:01:44,878
And that's it, it's not more.

35
00:01:44,961 --> 00:01:46,672
You're in the book!

36
00:01:46,756 --> 00:01:49,008
And yet I don't know you.

37
00:01:49,091 --> 00:01:50,927
What I do know about,
is my interest in you,

38
00:01:51,010 --> 00:01:52,428
-and that is real.
-Yeah, but still,

39
00:01:52,512 --> 00:01:54,388
you had to meet me first.

40
00:01:54,472 --> 00:01:57,016
I'm real, in front of you, now.

41
00:01:57,099 --> 00:01:58,643
SANDRA (laughs):
Yes, that you are.

42
00:01:58,726 --> 00:01:59,936
Yeah. Yeah.

43
00:02:00,019 --> 00:02:01,854
So, for you to start inventing,

44
00:02:01,938 --> 00:02:03,981
you need something real first.

45
00:02:04,065 --> 00:02:06,400
You say your books
always mix truth and fiction,

46
00:02:06,484 --> 00:02:08,778
and that makes us want
to figure out which is which.

47
00:02:08,861 --> 00:02:09,779
You want?

48
00:02:09,862 --> 00:02:10,863
ZOE: Is that your goal?

49
00:02:10,947 --> 00:02:11,906
What's...

50
00:02:11,989 --> 00:02:14,575
(chatting continues in distance)

51
00:02:14,659 --> 00:02:15,910
(sniffs)

52
00:02:15,993 --> 00:02:17,286
(in French)
Okay, get out.

53
00:02:21,832 --> 00:02:23,000
Snoop, come!

54
00:02:24,377 --> 00:02:26,796
Let's dry you off.
You're nice and clean.

55
00:02:27,088 --> 00:02:28,047
No more dirt.

56
00:02:28,130 --> 00:02:30,466
("P.I.M.P." by Bacao Rhythm & Steel Band
